                    <span>thomas more's utopia is a great work of fiction.  Using false pen names and creating false places (utopia is actually a fictional land) he escaped severe criminal punishment and still was able to tell an incredible philosophical tale.  Its fairly easy to read and its ideas are straight forward and logical.  A great work that started utopian literature.</span>
                  
